+# MCP Server Troubleshooting
+
+## Connection refused on port 8001
+
+1. Verify the MCP server is running: `pnpm run dev:mcp`
+2. Check if the port is already in use: `lsof -i :8001`
+3. Ensure your `.env.local` has the correct `MCP_PORT=8001`
+
+## OAuth2 token expired
+
+Tokens have a 1-hour lifetime. If you get 401 errors:
+
+1. Delete `gh-token-cache.json` next to `moltnet.json`
+2. Re-authenticate: the next API call will fetch a fresh token
+
+## SSE connection drops
+
+The MCP server uses Server-Sent Events. If connections drop:
+
+- Check for proxy/load balancer timeout settings (must be > 30s)
+- Verify `Transfer-Encoding: chunked` is not being stripped
